{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-12-20","name":"Hugh de Morville","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Hugh de Morville","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Hugh"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Morville"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"1138–1202","fullLifespan":"1138–1202","memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"DOCUMENT","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-101487-1645-33/dist.pdf?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/112612899","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-101487-1645-33/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"Morville in the Foundation for Medieval Genealogy","description":"Morville in the Foundation for Medieval Genealogy\n~http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/enguntlo.htm#_Toc25491904","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1138","birthPlace":{"address":"Kirkowald, Cumbria, England","geo":{"latitude":54.53065,"longitude":-3.07617,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1202","deathPlace":{"address":"Burgh by Sands, Cumberland, England","geo":{"latitude":54.9235,"longitude":-3.051,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"burialPlace":{"address":"England, United Kingdom","geo":{"latitude":52.4379,"longitude":-1.6496,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography\nLordships«/b»\nHugh inherited the barony of Burgh by Sands from his mother, which was then split between his daughters. Concerning the Barony of Appleby, Curwen writes:\n\nResearch Notes\nSGM remark:\n\nThere were at least three prominent 12th century men named Hugh de Morville. It is clear from several recent posts that they are easily confused. DNB is no doubt the cause of this.\n\nThe first Hugh was one of the murderers of Becket. There is chronicle evidence that his parents were Hugh de Morville and Beatrice de Beauchamp, and that he was lord of Knaresborough and Westmorland both of which he lost in rebellion in 1173/4. He probably dsp overseas.\n\nThe second was Hugh of Burgh by Sands. He succeeded his father Simon in 1167 and died in 1202. His mother was Ada Engaine and he had two daughters Ada and Joan.\n\nThe third Hugh was constable of Scotland and founder of Dryburgh Abbey. He held Cunningham and Lauderdale and died in 1162. His children were Richard, Hugh, Roger, Malcolm, John, Ada and Maud.","sourceList":[{"title":"Our royal, titled, noble and commoner ancestors","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://our-royal-titled-noble-and-commoner-ancestors.com/p195.htm#i5853","sourceUri":"QZQY-RFY"},{"title":"Wikipedia -Hugh de Morville, Husband of Helawise de Stuteville","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_III_de_Stuteville","sourceUri":"357G-63F"},{"title":"Morville in the Foundation for Medieval Genealogy ~ http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/enguntlo.htm#_Toc25491904 [See document in the Memories section]","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/enguntlo.htm#_Toc25491904","sourceUri":"SRYP-HPR"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1138","date":"1138","place":"Kirkowald, Cumbria, England"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1167","date":"1167","place":"Cumberland, England","age":"29","id":"MWGR-GZG"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1169","date":"after 1169","place":"Burgh-by-Sands, Cumberland, England","age":"32","id":"MQD3-STC"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1184","date":"1184","place":"Burgh By Sands, Cumberland, England","age":"46","id":"MJ3P-43B"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1188","date":"1188","place":"Burgh by Sands, Cumberland, England","age":"50","id":"9CM3-RKZ"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1202","date":"1202","place":"Burgh by Sands, Cumberland, England","age":"64"},{"name":"Burial","sources":"0","place":"England, United